#: ../appendix/login_windows.rst:4
msgid "PuTTY"
msgstr ""

#: ../appendix/login_windows.rst:6
msgid "If you are a Windows user, you can use some applications of SSH. Here, we recommend `PuTTY <https://www.chiark.greenend.org.uk/~sgtatham/putty/latest.html>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../appendix/login_windows.rst:8
msgid "**Step 1**"
msgstr ""

#: ../appendix/login_windows.rst:10
msgid "Download PuTTY."
msgstr ""

#: ../appendix/login_windows.rst:12
msgid "**Step 2**"
msgstr ""

#: ../appendix/login_windows.rst:14
msgid "Open PuTTY and click **Session** on the left tree-alike structure. Enter the IP address of the RPi in the text box under **Host Name (or IP address)** and **22** under **Port** (by default it is 22)."
msgstr ""

#: ../appendix/login_windows.rst:21
msgid "**Step 3**"
msgstr ""

#: ../appendix/login_windows.rst:23
msgid "Click **Open**. Note that when you first log in to the Raspberry Pi with the IP address, there prompts a security reminder. Just click **Yes**."
msgstr ""

#: ../appendix/login_windows.rst:26
msgid "**Step 4**"
msgstr ""

#: ../appendix/login_windows.rst:28
msgid "When the PuTTY window prompts \\\"**login as:**\\\", type in \\\"**pi**\\\" (the user name of the RPi), and **password**: \\\"raspberry\\\" (the default one, if you haven't changed it)."
msgstr ""

#: ../appendix/login_windows.rst:34
msgid "When you input the password, the characters do not display on window accordingly, which is normal. What you need is to input the correct password."
msgstr ""

#: ../appendix/login_windows.rst:36
msgid "If inactive appears next to PuTTY, it means that the connection has been broken and needs to be reconnected."
msgstr ""

#: ../appendix/login_windows.rst:41
msgid "**Step 5**"
msgstr ""

#: ../appendix/login_windows.rst:43
msgid "Here, we get the Raspberry Pi connected and it is time to conduct the next steps."
msgstr ""
